'''Duje Ćaleta-Car''' ({{IPA|hr|dǔːje tɕâleta tsâr}};<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=fF5mXhk%3D&keyword=Sv.|title=Dẉjam|quote=Dúje|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|access-date=23 February 2020|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=f11jWhg%3D&keyword=car|title=cȁr|quote=Cȁr|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|access-date=23 February 2020|language=hr}}</ref> born 17 September 1996) is a Croatian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#centre-back|centre-back]] for {{Spanish football updater|Real Sociedad}} club [[Real Sociedad]], on loan from {{French football updater|Lyon}} club [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]], and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/duje-aleta-car/266051/|title=D. Caleta-Car|website=Soccerway|access-date=3 February 2018}}</ref>

Ćaleta-Car was a member of the Croatian squad which ended as runners-up to [[France national football team|France]] in the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Ćaleta-Car joined [[FC Liefering]] in 2014 from [[FC Pasching]]. He made his [[Austrian Football First League]] debut with [[FC Liefering]] on 25 July 2014 against [[FAC Team für Wien]].<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/07/25/austria/1-liga/usk-anif/fac-team-fur-wien/1699975/|title=FC Liefering vs. FAC Team für Win - 25 July 2014 - Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|access-date=24 August 2014}}</ref>

===Red Bull Salzburg===
[[File:FC Salzburg versus S.S. Lazio Rom Euroleague-Viertelfinale (12. April 2018) 18.jpg|thumb|left|150px|Ćaleta-Car with Salzburg in 2018.]]
During the [[2017–18 FC Red Bull Salzburg season|2017–18 season]] Salzburg had their best ever European campaign. They finished top of their [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League group stage#Group I|group]], for a record fourth time, before beating [[Real Sociedad]] and [[Borussia Dortmund]] thus making their first ever appearance in a UEFA Europa League semi-final.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/0244-0e98bb008042-c1ca7adedb30-1000--salzburg-v-marseille-background/|title=Salzburg v Marseille background|last=UEFA.com|website=[[UEFA]]|date=27 April 2018 }}</ref> On 3 May 2018, he played in the [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League knockout phase#Semi-finals|Europa League semi-final]] as [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] played out a 1–2 away loss but a 3–2 aggregate win to secure a place in the [[2018 UEFA Europa League Final]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43998194|title=FC Red Bull Salzburg 2–1 Marseille|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=3 May 2018|access-date=3 May 2018}}</ref>

===Marseille===
[[File:Lens - Marseille (03-02-2021) 26.jpg|thumb|185px|Ćaleta-Car warming up for [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] in 2021.]]
On 20 July 2018, Ćaleta-Car joined Marseille on a five-year deal for a transfer fee of €19 million. Upon his arrival, Ćaleta-Car was given the squad shirt number 15.<ref>{{cite web |title=Duje Caleta-Car joins Les Olympiens! |url=https://www.om.net/en/videos/358138/duje-caleta-car-joins-les-olympiens |publisher=Olympique de Marseille |access-date=20 July 2018 |date=20 July 2018}}</ref>

On 29 September 2019, he scored his first goal for Marseille, the equalizer in a 1–1 draw with [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|date=2020-08-30|title=VIDEO: Velika večer Vatrenog! Do danas je u klubu zabio samo jednom, sinoć je mrežu tresao čak dva puta|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/le-championnat/video-velika-vecer-vatrenog-do-danas-je-u-klubu-zabio-samo-jednom-sinoc-je-mrezu-tresao-cak-dva-puta-15016282|access-date=2020-08-31|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr}}</ref>

At the start of the [[2020–21 Olympique de Marseille season|2020–21 season]], Ćaleta-Car scored a brace against [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]], converting assists of [[Florian Thauvin]], as Marseille won 3–2.<ref name=":0" /> At the end of the January 2021 transfer window, [[Premier League]] side [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] launched a £23 million bid to secure his services but the move failed to materialize as Marseille didn't have enough time to sign a replacement.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-02-01|title=Duje Caleta-Car fails to board flight after Liverpool agree transfer|url=https://metro.co.uk/2021/02/01/duje-caleta-car-fails-to-board-flight-after-liverpool-agree-transfer-13998109/|access-date=2021-02-28|website=Metro|language=en}}</ref>

=== Southampton ===
On 1 September 2022, Ćaleta-Car joined [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 September 2022 |title=Saints make deadline swoop for Ćaleta-Car |url=https://www.southamptonfc.com/news/2022-09-01/duje-caleta-car-announcement-southampton-marseille-transfer |access-date=1 September 2022 |website=Southampton FC}}</ref> On 1 October 2022, Ćaleta-Car made his [[Premier League]] debut in a 1–2 defeat against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Beardmore |first=Michael |date=1 October 2022 |title=Southampton 1–2 Everton |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63017882 |access-date=18 April 2023 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> In the [[EFL Cup]] semi-final first leg against [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] on 24 January 2023, Ćaleta-Car was given a second yellow card and sent off following a foul on [[Allan Saint-Maximin]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hunter |first=Laura |date=25 January 2023 |title=Southampton 0–1 Newcastle United |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11938/12794102/southampton-0-1-newcastle-joelinton-strike-gives-eddie-howes-side-advantage-in-carabao-cup-semi-final |access-date=18 April 2023 |website=Sky Sports}}</ref> On 1 March 2023, Ćaleta-Car scored his first professional goal for Southampton in a 1–2 shock defeat to [[Grimsby Town F.C.|Grimsby Town]] in the [[FA Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=1 March 2023 |title=Southampton 1–2 Grimsby Town |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/64799742 |access-date=18 April 2023 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He scored his first league goal on 21 April 2023 in a 3–3 away draw at Arsenal.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-04-20 |title=Premier League: Arsenal 3-3 Southampton - Gunners score two quick goals to level thriller |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/65344031 |access-date=2023-04-21}}</ref>

=== Lyon ===
On 2 August 2023, Ćaleta-Car joined [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 August 2023 |title=Ćaleta-Car joins Lyon on loan |url=https://www.southamptonfc.com/en/news/article/caleta-car-joins-lyon-on-loan |access-date=2 August 2023 |website=Southampton FC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=House |first=Alfie |date=2 August 2023 |title=Southampton's Duje Caleta-Car completes loan transfer to Lyon |url=https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/sport/23697565.southamptons-duje-caleta-car-completes-loan-transfer-lyon/ |access-date=2 August 2023 |website=Southern Daily Echo}}</ref> Ćaleta-Car made his debut for the club on 13 August 2023 in a 2–1 defeat to [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 August 2023 |title=Strasbourg 2–1 Lyon |url=https://www.ligue1.com/match?matchId=71645 |access-date=22 August 2023 |website=Ligue 1}}</ref> On 8 July 2024, he joined the club permanently and signed a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 July 2024 |title=L'Olympique Lyonnais lève les options d'achat de Duje Ćaleta-Car et mama baldé |url=https://www.ol.fr/fr/actualites/l-olympique-lyonnais-leve-les-options-d-achat-de-duje-caleta-car-et-mama-balde |access-date=8 July 2024 |website=Olympique Lyonnais |language=fr}}</ref>

====Loan to Real Sociedad====
On 1 August 2025, Ćaleta-Car moved to [[La Liga]] side [[Real Sociedad]] on a one-year loan deal with an option to buy for €3 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realsociedad.eus/es/noticias/detalle/acuerdo-para-la-cesion-de-duje-caleta-car|title=Acuerdo para la cesión de Duje Ćaleta-Car|trans-title=Agreement for the loan of Duje Ćaleta-Car|publisher=Real Sociedad|language=es|date=1 August 2025|accessdate=1 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:20150328 1427 U19 AUTHRV 1361.jpg|thumb|left|Ćaleta-Car with Croatia in 2015.]]
In October 2015, Ćaleta-Car received a first call-up for the [[Croatia national football team|senior national team]] for the [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group H|Euro 2016 qualifying]] matches against [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]] and [[Malta national football team|Malta]], as a replacement for injured [[Jozo Šimunović]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Celtic defender Jozo Šimunović will miss Croatia's qualifiers against Bulgaria and Malta due to injury, with Duje Ćaleta-Car called up as his replacement|url=http://hns-cff.hr/en/news/12324/caleta-car-replaces-simunovic-for-upcoming-matches/|access-date=17 November 2015|publisher=hns-cff.hr|date=2 October 2015}}</ref> He was in the first 27 players team called for the [[UEFA Euro 2016|Euro 2016]] but was dropped along with midfielder [[Alen Halilović]] and goalkeeper [[Dominik Livaković]].

In May 2018, he was named in Croatia's preliminary 32-man squad for the [[2018 World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Stephen|last=Crawford|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad {{!}} Final 23-man lists|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists-when-will-they-be-announced/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|url-status=dead|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230528150125/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists-when-will-they-be-announced/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|archive-date=28 May 2023}}</ref> On 3 June, he made his international debut in a [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]], coming on as a substitute for [[Vedran Ćorluka]] in the 52nd minute.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Branimir|last=Korać|title=Ćaleta-Car: "Ostvario mi se san nastupiti za reprezentaciju i to još protiv Brazila"|trans-title=Ćaleta-Car: "My dream has come true to play for the national team, even against Brazil"|url=https://sportnet.hr/vijesti/513039/nogomet-reprezentacija/caleta-car-ostvario-mi-se-san-nastupiti-za-reprezentaciju-i-to-jos-protiv-brazila/|website=Sportnet Croatia|date=6 June 2018|access-date=8 June 2024|language=hr}}</ref>

In June 2019, he refused to be part of [[Croatia national under-21 football team|Croatia]] [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship#Croatia|squad]] for [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2019 UEFA Under-21 Euro]], citing exhaustion and the club's demand to take a rest for the [[2019–20 Olympique de Marseille season|upcoming season]] as reasons. Soon it was discovered that the real reason was a vacation in the [[Maldives]] with his club teammate [[Nemanja Radonjić]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Otkrivamo zašto je Ćaleta-Car otkazao reprezentaciju! Ima nevjerojatan razlog|url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/otkrivamo-zasto-je-caleta-car-otkazao-reprezentaciju-ima-nevjerojatan-razlog-1324722|access-date=20 August 2019|publisher=[[Večernji list]]|date=8 June 2019|language=hr}}</ref> As a disciplinary action, he was the only [[outfield player]] who wasn't given even a minute of playing time in senior Croatia squad's June fixtures against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] and [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]] and was completely dropped ahead of September fixtures against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]] and [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=IZBORNIK DALIĆ PROTIV JEDNOG POTEZA NIJE MOGAO PRIJEĆI I KAZNIO VATRENOG KOJEG JE VODIO U RUSIJU Morao je znati da mu takva odluka neće dobro proći...|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/nogomet/reprezentacija/izbornik-dalic-protiv-jednog-poteza-nije-mogao-prijeci-i-kaznio-vatrenog-kojeg-je-vodio-u-rusiju-morao-je-znati-da-mu-takva-odluka-nece-dobro-proci/9255080/|access-date=20 August 2019|publisher=[[Sportske novosti]]|date=20 August 2019|language=hr}}</ref> In an interview with ''[[Sportske novosti]]'', he denied going on the vacation and said that the sole reason of not participating in the tournament was suggestion of his club coaches [[Andoni Zubizarreta]] and [[André Villas-Boas]] to take a rest instead since his [[2018–19 Olympique de Marseille season|previous season]] was not on the level it was expected to be, partially due to his participation in the World Cup the summer before, and that it was not his personal wish. He also claimed that the Croatia U21 manager [[Nenad Gračan]] "had lied and had disappointed him", that "it had hurt him to read the lies of the media" about the vacation, and that he accepted senior Croatia squad manager [[Zlatko Dalić]]'s decision to drop him from the team.<ref>{{cite news|title=ODBAČENI VATRENI SVE OTKRIO: 'POSTAO SAM GLAVNI NEGATIVAC U HRVATSKOJ, A OVO JE ISTINA' 'Gračan je lagao i razočarao me! A Dalićevu kaznu prihvaćam'|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/planet-hrvatska/odbaceni-vatreni-sve-otkrio-postao-sam-glavni-negativac-u-hrvatskoj-a-ovo-je-istina-gracan-je-lagao-i-razocarao-me-a-dalicevu-kaznu-prihvacam/9271190|access-date=24 August 2019|publisher=[[Sportske novosti]]|date=23 August 2019|language=hr}}</ref>

He was called up again ahead of Croatia's November fixtures against Slovakia and [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] following suspensions of the standard starting defenders [[Dejan Lovren]] and [[Domagoj Vida]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Izbornik Dalić Objavio Službeni Popis i Potvrdio NagaĐanja Vraća u reprezentaciju 'nestašnog' braniča: Duje Ćaleta-Car pozvan za Slovačku|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/nogomet/reprezentacija/izbornik-dalic-objavio-sluzbeni-popis-i-potvrdio-nagadanja-vraca-u-reprezentaciju-nestasnog-branica-duje-caleta-car-pozvan-za-slovacku/9544910/|access-date=29 October 2019|publisher=[[Sportske novosti]]|date=28 August 2019|language=hr}}</ref> He was a starter in the decisive match against the former opponent that ended in a 3–1 victory, leading Croatia to [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group E|qualify]] for the [[UEFA Euro 2020|Euro 2020]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/euro2020/napokon-je-gotovo-hrvatska-rijetko-videnim-preokretom-izborila-euro-slovaci-su-zabili-a-onda-je-zlatko-dalic-povukao-potez-kvalifikacija/9622936/|title=Napokon je Gotovo, Hrvatska Rijetko ViĐenim Preokreto, Izborika Euro! Slovaci su zabili, a onda je Zlatko Dalić povukao potez kvalifikacija|date=16 November 2019|publisher=[[Sportske novosti]]|access-date=17 November 2019|language=hr}}</ref>

==Personal life==
In May 2021, Ćaleta-Car married Adriana Đurđević in a civil ceremony at the top of the [[Revelin Fortress]] in Đurđević's native [[Dubrovnik]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-06-01|title=Presretni mladenci! Donosimo ekskluzivne fotografije s vjenčanja Duje Ćalete-Cara i njegove Adriane!|url=https://www.gloria.hr/gl/magazin/presretni-mladenci-donosimo-ekskluzivne-fotografije-s-vjencanja-duje-calete-cara-i-njegove-adriane-15077565|url-status=live|access-date=2021-06-03|website=Gloria|language=hr-hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603162051/https://www.gloria.hr/gl/magazin/presretni-mladenci-donosimo-ekskluzivne-fotografije-s-vjencanja-duje-calete-cara-i-njegove-adriane-15077565 |archive-date=3 June 2021 }}</ref> In August 2021, Ćaleta-Car and Đurđević became parents of a baby son,<ref>{{Cite web|last=Š. P.|date=2021-08-23|title=Duje Ćaleta-Car postao otac, u njegovim Bilicama naveliko se slavi|url=https://sibenskiportal.hr/scenoskop/lifestyle/duje-caleta-car-postao-otac-u-njegovim-bilicama-naveliko-se-slavi/|url-status=live|access-date=2021-08-27|website=Šibenski portal|language=hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210823141921/https://sibenskiportal.hr/scenoskop/lifestyle/duje-caleta-car-postao-otac-u-njegovim-bilicama-naveliko-se-slavi/ |archive-date=23 August 2021 }}</ref> whom they named Mauro.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Đ. S.|date=2021-08-28|title=Supruga Ćalete-Cara stigla je kući sa sinom, vesela fotografija slučajno je otkrila i mališanovo ime!|url=https://dnevnik.hr/showbuzz/celebrity/adriana-i-duje-caleta-car-otkrili-ime-sincica---664563.html|url-status=live|access-date=2022-01-16|website=Dnevnik.hr|language=hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828152321/https://dnevnik.hr/showbuzz/celebrity/adriana-i-duje-caleta-car-otkrili-ime-sincica---664563.html |archive-date=28 August 2021 }}</ref> In June 2022, Ćaleta-Car and Đurđević married in a church ceremony in the [[Collegium Ragusinum|St. Ignatius Church]] in Dubrovnik.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tolić |first=Dolores |date=2022-06-04 |title=FOTO: Pogledajte bajkovito vjenčanje Duje Ćalete-Cara! Stigao i Bruno Petković sa zaručnicom... |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/nogomet-mix/pogledajte-bajkovito-vjencanje-duje-calete-cara-stigao-i-bruno-petkovic-sa-zarucnicom-15206395 |access-date=2022-06-04 |website=Sportske novosti |language=hr-hr}}</ref>

